chapter:
Using &MiKTeX;
Getting Started
If you have never used &TeX; before, then it is recommendable
local guide
to work through one of the &TeX;/&LaTeX; tutorials. A good starting point is this entry in the UK &TeX; &FAQ;: http://www.tex.ac.uk/cgi-bin/texfaq2html?label=tutorials*.
&MiKTeX; doesn't differ very much from any other &TeX; system you might have used before. Typesetting with &MiKTeX; involves these steps:
Edit the &LaTeX; source with your favourite text document editor.
Compile the &LaTeX; source into a &DVI; file, i.e., say something like latex MyMastersThesis.
Open the result by double-clicking the &DVI; file (e.g., MyMastersThesis.dvi) in Windows Explorer.
You usually use a &LaTeX; editor to carry out these steps. The most prominent ones are listed here: http://www.tex.ac.uk/cgi-bin/texfaq2html?label=editors.
